cmplsLsrExtStdMIB.name: cmplsLsrExtStdMIB

cmplsXCExtTable.name: cmplsXCExtTable
cmplsXCExtTable.reference: 1. Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS) Label Switching Router (LSR) Management Information Base (MIB), RFC 3813.
cmplsXCExtTable.description: This table sparse augments the mplsXCTable of MPLS-LSR-STD-MIB [RFC3813] to provide MPLS-TP specific information about associated tunnel information

cmplsXCExtEntry.name: cmplsXCExtEntry
cmplsXCExtEntry.reference: 1. Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS) Label Switching Router (LSR) Management Information Base (MIB), RFC 3813.
cmplsXCExtEntry.description: An entry in this table extends the cross connect information represented by an entry in the mplsXCTable in MPLS-LSR-STD-MIB [RFC3813] through a sparse augmentation. An entry can be created by a network administrator via SNMP SET commands, or in response to signaling protocol events.

cmplsXCExtTunnelPointer.name: cmplsXCExtTunnelPointer
cmplsXCExtTunnelPointer.reference: 1. Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS) Label Switching Router (LSR) Management Information Base (MIB), RFC 3813.
cmplsXCExtTunnelPointer.description: This object indicates the back pointer to the tunnel entry segment. This object cannot be modified if mplsXCRowStatus for the corresponding entry in the mplsXCTable is active(1).

cmplsXCOppositeDirXCPtr.name: cmplsXCOppositeDirXCPtr
cmplsXCOppositeDirXCPtr.reference: 1. Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS) Label Switching Router (LSR) Management Information Base (MIB), RFC 3813.
cmplsXCOppositeDirXCPtr.description: This object indicates the pointer to the opposite direction XC entry. This object cannot be modified if mplsXCRowStatus for the corresponding entry in the mplsXCTable is active(1).

cmplsLsrExtModuleFullCompliance.name: cmplsLsrExtModuleFullCompliance
cmplsLsrExtModuleFullCompliance.description: Compliance statement for agents that provide full support for MPLS-LSR-EXT-STD-MIB. The mandatory group has to be implemented by all LSRs that originate, terminate, or act as transit for TE-LSPs/tunnels. In addition, depending on the type of tunnels supported, other groups become mandatory as explained below.

cmplsLsrExtModuleReadOnlyCompliance.name: cmplsLsrExtModuleReadOnlyCompliance
cmplsLsrExtModuleReadOnlyCompliance.description: Compliance requirement for implementations that only provide read-only support for MPLS-LSR-EXT-STD-MIB. Such devices can then be monitored but cannot be configured using this MIB module.

cmplsXCExtGroup.name: cmplsXCExtGroup
cmplsXCExtGroup.description: This object should be supported in order to access the tunnel entry from XC entry.
